author: xsteve
msg: Allow the user to enter the username/passwd
* trunk/contrib/client-side/psvn/psvn.el:
(svn-process-filter): Some improvements to prepare the questioning for
the password of a user
(svn-process-send-string): Added the optional parameter send-passwd
to suppress the display of a sent passwd
That feature is experimental at the moment and can be enabled via
(setq svn-status-use-process-filter t)

author: maxb
msg: Tests do not need to install a berkeley errcall.
Since 1.1, the Subversion core handles this itself.
* subversion/tests/fs-helpers.c (berkeley_error_handler): Delete.
(svn_test__create_fs, svn_test__create_repos):
Do not call svn_fs_set_berkeley_errcall().

author: maxb
msg: * STATUS [1.2]: Nominate a FSFS test failure fix.

author: maxb
msg: Avoid spurious test failures when using FSFS and test repositories remain on
disk from a previous test run.
* subversion/tests/fs-helpers.c (svn_test__create_fs):
Use svn_fs_delete_fs(), not svn_fs_delete_berkeley().

author: maxb
msg: Fix an error leak, and decomplicate code.
* subversion/libsvn_client/revert.c (svn_client_revert, revert): Shuffle code
between the main function and the static helper for a more logical layout,
and to fix an error leak.
